The Zamolodchikov metric $G_{OO}$ or the norm  of this operator is defined by
 \begin{equation}\label{z-met} 
G_{OO}\, a^2 = \lim_{\epsilon\rightarrow 0} \epsilon^4 \langle
{\cal O} ( \tau, \sigma+ \epsilon)
{\cal O} ( \tau, \sigma) \rangle.
\end{equation}
Note that from the expansions of the functions $f$ and $g$ in the appendix this
operator is well defined for $0<\alpha<1$.
To evaluate the Zamolodchikov metric it is 
convenient  to appeal to the formula relating it to the
Weil-Petersson metric in the space of metrics 
\cite{Candelas:1990qn} which is given by
